The paper deals with facility location problems on planar graphs and the 2-dimensional plane, which are classic topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of Voronoi diagrams is a central technique in the algorithm design, which is also a common tool in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of packing and covering constraints, which are related to combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper are based on the design of geometric QPTASs, which is a topic in approximation algorithms (cs.CC). Finally, the paper provides evidence that packing problems have faster algorithms than covering problems for a more general class of objects, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.GT).
